dsucsuSysTable.name: dsucsuSysTable
dsucsuSysTable.description: A list of system level attributes describing the addressed node.

dsucsuSysSlot.name: dsucsuSysSlot
dsucsuSysSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuSysNode.name: dsucsuSysNode
dsucsuSysNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuSysName.name: dsucsuSysName
dsucsuSysName.description: The unique name of the node accessed

dsucsuSysType.name: dsucsuSysType
dsucsuSysType.description: A desciption of the system model: ie. ONS400, FNS400, ONS1000X, BLACK BOX FT1-4

dsucsuSysSoftRev.name: dsucsuSysSoftRev
dsucsuSysSoftRev.description: Displays the Software Revision of the accessed node.

dsucsuSysHardRev.name: dsucsuSysHardRev
dsucsuSysHardRev.description: Displays the Hardware Revision of the accessed node.

dsucsuSysNumChan.name: dsucsuSysNumChan
dsucsuSysNumChan.description: The number of channels that are installed on the node.

dsucsuCfgNetSlot.name: dsucsuCfgNetSlot
dsucsuCfgNetSlot.description: The NEST slot to which the TyLink card is attached.

dsucsuCfgNetNode.name: dsucsuCfgNetNode
dsucsuCfgNetNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuCfgNetInterface.name: dsucsuCfgNetInterface
dsucsuCfgNetInterface.description: The interface type for 3000N. For a T1 line, NETWORK or DSX-1 is valid.

dsucsuCfgNetCoding.name: dsucsuCfgNetCoding
dsucsuCfgNetCoding.description: The encoding scheme for the line. For a T1 line, AMI and B8ZS are valid. For an E1 line, AMI and HDB3 are valid.

dsucsuCfgNetClockSource.name: dsucsuCfgNetClockSource
dsucsuCfgNetClockSource.description: The aggregate timing for the addressed node.

dsucsuCfgNetCsuLBO.name: dsucsuCfgNetCsuLBO
dsucsuCfgNetCsuLBO.description: The setting of the Line Buildout switch. Setting must be db_0 if network interface is DSX-1.

dsucsuCfgNetCsuDensity.name: dsucsuCfgNetCsuDensity
dsucsuCfgNetCsuDensity.description: The setting of the one stuffing option. Inserts a 1 into the 8th, 16th, or 64th bit position (depending on the selection) if the previous 7 bits were 0's.

dsucsuCfgNetRateMultiples.name: dsucsuCfgNetRateMultiples
dsucsuCfgNetRateMultiples.description: The channel rate multiples for each of the ports.

dsucsuCfgNetOutputPulse.name: dsucsuCfgNetOutputPulse
dsucsuCfgNetOutputPulse.description: The distance to the CSU in feet.

dsucsuCfgNetTs16.name: dsucsuCfgNetTs16
dsucsuCfgNetTs16.description: The E1 Timeslot 16 value. Valid values are data and multiframe alignment.

dsucsuCfgDteChanEntry.name: dsucsuCfgDteChanEntry
dsucsuCfgDteChanEntry.description: DTE Channel Configuration Object for a DSU/CSU

dsucsuCfgDteChanSlot.name: dsucsuCfgDteChanSlot
dsucsuCfgDteChanSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuCfgDteChanNode.name: dsucsuCfgDteChanNode
dsucsuCfgDteChanNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuCfgDteChanRate.name: dsucsuCfgDteChanRate
dsucsuCfgDteChanRate.description: The Data rate in kilobits per second. The rate is dependent on the setting of the Aggregate DTE channel multiples.

dsucsuCfgDteChanStartDs0.name: dsucsuCfgDteChanStartDs0
dsucsuCfgDteChanStartDs0.description: The starting DS0 for the addressed channel's data.

dsucsuCfgDteChanClockInvert.name: dsucsuCfgDteChanClockInvert
dsucsuCfgDteChanClockInvert.description: The DTE channel Clock Invert setting.

dsucsuCfgDteChanDataInvert.name: dsucsuCfgDteChanDataInvert
dsucsuCfgDteChanDataInvert.description: The DTE channel Data Invert setting.

dsucsuCfgFrmChanEntry.name: dsucsuCfgFrmChanEntry
dsucsuCfgFrmChanEntry.description: Framed Channel Configuration Object for a DSU/CSU

dsucsuCfgFrmChanSlot.name: dsucsuCfgFrmChanSlot
dsucsuCfgFrmChanSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuCfgFrmChanNode.name: dsucsuCfgFrmChanNode
dsucsuCfgFrmChanNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuCfgFrmChanNumDs0.name: dsucsuCfgFrmChanNumDs0
dsucsuCfgFrmChanNumDs0.description: The number of DS0's on the network side.

dsucsuCfgFrmChanStartDs0.name: dsucsuCfgFrmChanStartDs0
dsucsuCfgFrmChanStartDs0.description: The starting DS0 on the network side.

dsucsuCfgFrmChanDteStartDs0.name: dsucsuCfgFrmChanDteStartDs0
dsucsuCfgFrmChanDteStartDs0.description: The starting DS0 on the framed channel.

dsucsuCfgFrmChanOutputPulse.name: dsucsuCfgFrmChanOutputPulse
dsucsuCfgFrmChanOutputPulse.description: The cabling distance from the PBX to the PBX channel port in feet.

dsucsuConfigSupEntry.name: dsucsuConfigSupEntry
dsucsuConfigSupEntry.description: Inband Supervisory Configuration Object for a DSU/CSU

dsucsuConfigSupSlot.name: dsucsuConfigSupSlot
dsucsuConfigSupSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuConfigSupNode.name: dsucsuConfigSupNode
dsucsuConfigSupNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuConfigSupIndex.name: dsucsuConfigSupIndex
dsucsuConfigSupIndex.description: The Supervisory channel index. Index 1 refers to supervisory channel A. Index 2 refers to supervisory channel B.

dsucsuConfigSupDs0.name: dsucsuConfigSupDs0
dsucsuConfigSupDs0.description: The DS0 to place the Supervisory channel in.

dsucsuCfgSupAuxEntry.name: dsucsuCfgSupAuxEntry
dsucsuCfgSupAuxEntry.description: Auxilary Supervisory Configuration Object for a DSU/CSU

dsucsuCfgSupAuxSlot.name: dsucsuCfgSupAuxSlot
dsucsuCfgSupAuxSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuCfgSupAuxNode.name: dsucsuCfgSupAuxNode
dsucsuCfgSupAuxNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuCfgSupAuxIndex.name: dsucsuCfgSupAuxIndex
dsucsuCfgSupAuxIndex.description: Auxillary Supervisory Channel Configuration Index Index 1 refers to FDL supervisory on PORT 1. Index 2 refers to FDL supervisory on PORT 2.

dsucsuCfgSupAuxFdl.name: dsucsuCfgSupAuxFdl
dsucsuCfgSupAuxFdl.description: Places the supervisory link bits within the Facility Data Link bits of the Extended Superframe.

dsucsuActvConfTable.name: dsucsuActvConfTable
dsucsuActvConfTable.description: Activate a stored configuration on the selected node.

dsucsuActvConfSlot.name: dsucsuActvConfSlot
dsucsuActvConfSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuActvConfNode.name: dsucsuActvConfNode
dsucsuActvConfNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuActvConfIndex.name: dsucsuActvConfIndex
dsucsuActvConfIndex.description: Activate one of the four stored configurations.

dsucsuEventDesTable.name: dsucsuEventDesTable
dsucsuEventDesTable.description: Table of event destinations. Events or alarms detected by a node can be reported to up to two destinations. The operator can set or clear either or both of these destinations via this Table.

dsucsuEventDesEntry.name: dsucsuEventDesEntry
dsucsuEventDesEntry.description: Entry in the table of event destinations.

dsucsuEventDesSlot.name: dsucsuEventDesSlot
dsucsuEventDesSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuEventDesNode.name: dsucsuEventDesNode
dsucsuEventDesNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuEventNameIndx.name: dsucsuEventNameIndx
dsucsuEventNameIndx.description: The unique name of the node accessed.

dsucsuEventDesName1.name: dsucsuEventDesName1
dsucsuEventDesName1.description: The name of the node/PC where the alarms will be sent to.

dsucsuEventDesName2.name: dsucsuEventDesName2
dsucsuEventDesName2.description: The name of the alternate node/PC where the alarms will be sent to.

dsucsuEventClrDest.name: dsucsuEventClrDest
dsucsuEventClrDest.description: Clears the destination(s) for the reporting of alarms.

dsucsuCfgMaintSlot.name: dsucsuCfgMaintSlot
dsucsuCfgMaintSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuCfgMaintNode.name: dsucsuCfgMaintNode
dsucsuCfgMaintNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuCfgMaintChanType.name: dsucsuCfgMaintChanType
dsucsuCfgMaintChanType.description: The type of data passed over the Maint. port.

dsucsuCfgMaintFlowCtrl.name: dsucsuCfgMaintFlowCtrl
dsucsuCfgMaintFlowCtrl.description: Flow Control for the Maint. port.

dsucsuCfgMaintStopBits.name: dsucsuCfgMaintStopBits
dsucsuCfgMaintStopBits.description: Number of Stopbits for the Maint. port.

dsucsuCfgMaintBaud.name: dsucsuCfgMaintBaud
dsucsuCfgMaintBaud.description: Baud rate for the Maint. port.

dsucsuCfgCommSlot.name: dsucsuCfgCommSlot
dsucsuCfgCommSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuCfgCommNode.name: dsucsuCfgCommNode
dsucsuCfgCommNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuCfgCommChanType.name: dsucsuCfgCommChanType
dsucsuCfgCommChanType.description: The type of data passed over the Communication port.

dsucsuCfgCommFlowCtrl.name: dsucsuCfgCommFlowCtrl
dsucsuCfgCommFlowCtrl.description: Flow Control for the Communication port.

dsucsuCfgCommStopBits.name: dsucsuCfgCommStopBits
dsucsuCfgCommStopBits.description: Number of Stopbits for the Communication port.

dsucsuCfgCommBaud.name: dsucsuCfgCommBaud
dsucsuCfgCommBaud.description: Baud rate for the Communication port.

dsucsuCfgBrdSlot.name: dsucsuCfgBrdSlot
dsucsuCfgBrdSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuCfgBrdNode.name: dsucsuCfgBrdNode
dsucsuCfgBrdNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuCfgBrdTiming.name: dsucsuCfgBrdTiming
dsucsuCfgBrdTiming.description: The Board Level Timing for a 3000N.

dsucsuCfgAutoAssignTable.name: dsucsuCfgAutoAssignTable
dsucsuCfgAutoAssignTable.description: Automatically assign the proper amount of bandwidth.

dsucsuConnAutoSlot.name: dsucsuConnAutoSlot
dsucsuConnAutoSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuConnAutoNode.name: dsucsuConnAutoNode
dsucsuConnAutoNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuConnAutoSrcPort.name: dsucsuConnAutoSrcPort
dsucsuConnAutoSrcPort.description: Index to the 3000N source port of interest. 3000N supports two DTE-V35/RS-499 DATA ports (P3-P4).

dsucsuConnAutoStartDS0.name: dsucsuConnAutoStartDS0
dsucsuConnAutoStartDS0.description: Port1/2 includes 24 DS0's. This value is the starting DS0 used by the node to allocate DS0s to meet port(3-4)-dte requirements. Sequential, contiguous DS0s are assigned. The number of DS0s required is based upon the DTE Data Rate and DTE Channel Mapping. The node's response to an entry may be gathered by querying dsucsuConnAutoStatus. To assign DS0s in a non-contiguous format, use the CfgEditConnTable.

dsucsuConnAutoDestPort.name: dsucsuConnAutoDestPort
dsucsuConnAutoDestPort.description: Selects the port for which DS0s are automatically allocated to one of the T1 network ports. Node software may not allow connection of port1 to port1.

dsucsuConnAutoType.name: dsucsuConnAutoType
dsucsuConnAutoType.description: Defines the type of traffic being transported. The 3000N supports data (1) or voice (2). The selected type will be assigned to all DS0s.

dsucsuConnDteRate.name: dsucsuConnDteRate
dsucsuConnDteRate.description: Data rate of the DTE port. Can be chaged from the CfgDteTable.

dsucsuConnDteDensity.name: dsucsuConnDteDensity
dsucsuConnDteDensity.description: Channel/DS0 format for the DTE port. Can be changed from the CfgDteTable.

dsucsuConnDs0Required.name: dsucsuConnDs0Required
dsucsuConnDs0Required.description: The number of DS0s required by the node's DTE port. This is based upon the DTE data rate and channel density selections.

dsucsuConnAutoStatus.name: dsucsuConnAutoStatus
dsucsuConnAutoStatus.description: Queries the node's connection status. Code will be returned when a connection set or update is rejected or accepted.

dsucsuConnAutoUpdateCmd.name: dsucsuConnAutoUpdateCmd
dsucsuConnAutoUpdateCmd.description: Updates the connections with the edit buffer. The edit buffer is comprised of any changes sent (set) from the dsucsuCfgAutoAssignEntry.

dsucsuCfgCurrentConnTable.name: dsucsuCfgCurrentConnTable
dsucsuCfgCurrentConnTable.description: Retrieves node's active connections assignments for display only. To edit connections, use CfgConnAutoAssign or CfgEditConnTable.

dsucsuCfgCurrentConnections.name: dsucsuCfgCurrentConnections
dsucsuCfgCurrentConnections.description: An entry in the Current Connections Table.

dsucsuSlot.name: dsucsuSlot
dsucsuSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuNode.name: dsucsuNode
dsucsuNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuT1Index.name: dsucsuT1Index
dsucsuT1Index.description: Index to T1 network port of interest. The 3000N supports two NETWORK/DSX-1 ports.

dsucsuDs0.name: dsucsuDs0
dsucsuDs0.description: DS0 number 1 through 24 corresponding to the T1 network port index.

dsucsuDtePort.name: dsucsuDtePort
dsucsuDtePort.description: DS0 assignment for indexed T1 network port. After making any adjustments to the connections, the dsucsuCfgConnUpdateCmd must be sent. Node software may not permit port 1 connections to itself.

dsucsuType.name: dsucsuType
dsucsuType.description: Defines the type of traffic being transported. The 3000N supports data (1) or voice (2).

dsucsuCfgEditConnTable.name: dsucsuCfgEditConnTable
dsucsuCfgEditConnTable.description: Manually assign the proper amount of bandwidth.

dsucsuCfgEditConnEntry.name: dsucsuCfgEditConnEntry
dsucsuCfgEditConnEntry.description: Edits current DS0 assignment. After making any adjustments to the connections, the dsucsuCfgConnUpdateCmd must be sent.

dsucsuConnSlot.name: dsucsuConnSlot
dsucsuConnSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuConnNode.name: dsucsuConnNode
dsucsuConnNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuConnSrcPort.name: dsucsuConnSrcPort
dsucsuConnSrcPort.description: Index to the source port of interest. The 3000N supports two NETWORK/DSX-1 and two DTE ports.

dsucsuConnSrcDs0.name: dsucsuConnSrcDs0
dsucsuConnSrcDs0.description: The source DS0 number 1 through 24 corresponding to the T1 network port index

dsucsuConnDestPort.name: dsucsuConnDestPort
dsucsuConnDestPort.description: Index to the destination port of interest. The 3000N supports two NETWORK/DSX-1 and two DTE ports.

dsucsuConnDestDs0.name: dsucsuConnDestDs0
dsucsuConnDestDs0.description: DS0 assignment for indexed T1 network port. After making any adjustments to the connections, the dsucsuConnUpdateCmd must be sent. Node software may not permit connections between the same port and itself.

dsucsuConnType.name: dsucsuConnType
dsucsuConnType.description: Defines the type of traffic being transported. The 3000N supports data (1) or voice (2).

dsucsuConnNumDs0s.name: dsucsuConnNumDs0s
dsucsuConnNumDs0s.description: The total number of Ds0s to be connected. The number of Ds0s must be between 1 and 24.

dsucsuConnSetStatus.name: dsucsuConnSetStatus
dsucsuConnSetStatus.description: Displays node status from the last SNMP issed set command.

dsucsuConnConnect.name: dsucsuConnConnect
dsucsuConnConnect.description: Updates the connections with the edit buffer. The edit buffer is comprised of any changes sent (set) from the CfgEditConnTable.

dsucsuConnUpdateRequired.name: dsucsuConnUpdateRequired
dsucsuConnUpdateRequired.description: Displays node status from the last connection update.

dsucsuConnUpdateCmd.name: dsucsuConnUpdateCmd
dsucsuConnUpdateCmd.description: Sends the updated connections from the edit buffer to the node. The edit buffer is comprised of any changes sent (set) from the CfgEditConnTable.

dsucsuConnClearEditBuff.name: dsucsuConnClearEditBuff
dsucsuConnClearEditBuff.description: Removes all changes from edit buffer. The edit buffer is comprised of any changes sent (set) from the CfgEditConnTable.

dsucsuDiagNetTable.name: dsucsuDiagNetTable
dsucsuDiagNetTable.description: A list of Network Diagnostic attributes. Loopbacks, tests and their respective results can be initiated, cancelled and examined.

dsucsuDiagNetSlot.name: dsucsuDiagNetSlot
dsucsuDiagNetSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuDiagNetNode.name: dsucsuDiagNetNode
dsucsuDiagNetNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuDiagNetIndex.name: dsucsuDiagNetIndex
dsucsuDiagNetIndex.description: The network number to be examined for a particular node (3000N only).

dsucsuDiagNetLclNetAggLpbk.name: dsucsuDiagNetLclNetAggLpbk
dsucsuDiagNetLclNetAggLpbk.description: Enables the operator to control and examine the local aggregate loopback. This loopback occurs on the net side of the local transmit and receive logic. The unit continues to transmit data across the network and also loops the data back to its own receiver circuitry.

dsucsuDiagNetLclNetLpbk.name: dsucsuDiagNetLclNetLpbk
dsucsuDiagNetLclNetLpbk.description: Enables the operator to control and examine the local network loopback. This loopback allows the operator to disconnect the side of the network by transmitting the data recovered from the network.

dsucsuDiagNetLclNetPayload.name: dsucsuDiagNetLclNetPayload
dsucsuDiagNetLclNetPayload.description: Enables the operator to control and examine the network payload loopback. This loopback occurs on the net side of the local transmit and receive logic. The unit continues to transmit data across the network and also loops the data back to its own receiver circuitry.

dsucsuDiagNetLclNetBiDir.name: dsucsuDiagNetLclNetBiDir
dsucsuDiagNetLclNetBiDir.description: Enables the operator to control and examine the local network loopback. This loopback allows the operator to disconnect the side of the network by transmitting the data recovered from the network in both directions.

dsucsuDiagNetRemCsuLpbk.name: dsucsuDiagNetRemCsuLpbk
dsucsuDiagNetRemCsuLpbk.description: Enables the operator to control and examine the remote CSU loopback. This loopback allows the operator to test the operation of the local channel, the aggregate and the remote CSU.

dsucsuDiagNetRemDsuLpbk.name: dsucsuDiagNetRemDsuLpbk
dsucsuDiagNetRemDsuLpbk.description: Enables the operator to control and examine the remote aggregate loopback. This loopback allows the operator to test the entire system from the local unit through the network to the remote node's transmit and receive front end.

dsucsuDiagNetEvElapTime.name: dsucsuDiagNetEvElapTime
dsucsuDiagNetEvElapTime.description: The time elapsed since the Event Test started. The new Event Test commences as soon as the previous Event Test registers are cleared.

dsucsuDiagNetEvCRC6Err.name: dsucsuDiagNetEvCRC6Err
dsucsuDiagNetEvCRC6Err.description: The number of CRC6 errors encountered during the Event Test period.

dsucsuDiagNetEvOofErr.name: dsucsuDiagNetEvOofErr
dsucsuDiagNetEvOofErr.description: The number of Out-Of-Frame errors encountered during the Event Test period.

dsucsuDiagNetErrEvents.name: dsucsuDiagNetErrEvents
dsucsuDiagNetErrEvents.description: The number of Errored Events encountered during the Event Test period.

dsucsuDiagNetClearEvReg.name: dsucsuDiagNetClearEvReg
dsucsuDiagNetClearEvReg.description: Clear all the Event Test registers. Automatically initiates a new Event Test.

dsucsuDiagDteTable.name: dsucsuDiagDteTable
dsucsuDiagDteTable.description: A list of DTE channel diagnostics.

dsucsuDiagDteSlot.name: dsucsuDiagDteSlot
dsucsuDiagDteSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuDiagDteNode.name: dsucsuDiagDteNode
dsucsuDiagDteNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuDiagDteIndex.name: dsucsuDiagDteIndex
dsucsuDiagDteIndex.description: The channel number to be examined for a particular node.

dsucsuDiagDteLocalBiDir.name: dsucsuDiagDteLocalBiDir
dsucsuDiagDteLocalBiDir.description: This selection displays the status or controls the Local Channel Loopback for the selected channel. This is a local turnaround and is bi-directional.

dsucsuDiagDteLocalPayload.name: dsucsuDiagDteLocalPayload
dsucsuDiagDteLocalPayload.description: This selection displays the status or controls the Local Payload Channel Loopback for the selected channel.

dsucsuDiagDteRemLpbk.name: dsucsuDiagDteRemLpbk
dsucsuDiagDteRemLpbk.description: This selection displays the status or controls the Channel Remote Loopback for the selected channel. This loopback transmits a code to the remote node which will enable or disable a diagnostic loopback at the addressed channel.

dsucsuDiagDteBertTestAct.name: dsucsuDiagDteBertTestAct
dsucsuDiagDteBertTestAct.description: BERT test related actions: a: Starts a BERT test on a channel, b: Stops a BERT test on a channel, c: Inject Errors while the BERT test is running, d: Clears BERT test errors.

dsucsuDiagDteBertHourStrt.name: dsucsuDiagDteBertHourStrt
dsucsuDiagDteBertHourStrt.description: Displays the hour that the BERT test started.

dsucsuDiagDteBertMinStrt.name: dsucsuDiagDteBertMinStrt
dsucsuDiagDteBertMinStrt.description: Displays th minute that BERT test started.

dsucsuDiagDteBertTimeElaps.name: dsucsuDiagDteBertTimeElaps
dsucsuDiagDteBertTimeElaps.description: Elapsed time since the BERT Test started

dsucsuDiagDteBertErrors.name: dsucsuDiagDteBertErrors
dsucsuDiagDteBertErrors.description: Number of BERT test errors encountered during the BERT Test.

dsucsuDiagFrmTable.name: dsucsuDiagFrmTable
dsucsuDiagFrmTable.description: A list of framed channel diagnostics.

dsucsuDiagFrmSlot.name: dsucsuDiagFrmSlot
dsucsuDiagFrmSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuDiagFrmNode.name: dsucsuDiagFrmNode
dsucsuDiagFrmNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuDiagFrmIndex.name: dsucsuDiagFrmIndex
dsucsuDiagFrmIndex.description: The channel number to be examined for a particular node.

dsucsuDiagFrmLclLpbk.name: dsucsuDiagFrmLclLpbk
dsucsuDiagFrmLclLpbk.description: This selection displays the status or controls the Local Channel Loopback for the selected channel. This is a local turnaround and is bi-directional.

dsucsuDiagFrmLclPayload.name: dsucsuDiagFrmLclPayload
dsucsuDiagFrmLclPayload.description: This selection displays the status or controls the Channel Remote Loopback for the selected channel. This loopback transmits a code to the remote node which will enable or disable a diagnostic loopback at the addressed channel. This selection is applicable only for DSX type channels.

dsucsuDiagFrmLclBiDir.name: dsucsuDiagFrmLclBiDir
dsucsuDiagFrmLclBiDir.description: This selection displays the status or controls the DSX Loopback for the selected channel. This selection is applicable only for DSX channels.

dsucsuDiagFrmRemLpbk.name: dsucsuDiagFrmRemLpbk
dsucsuDiagFrmRemLpbk.description: This selection displays the status or controls the Local Channel Loopback for the selected channel. This loopback transmits a code to the remote node which will enable or disable a diagnostic loopback at the addressed channel. This selection is applicable only for DSX channels.

dsucsuDiagFrmLclDte.name: dsucsuDiagFrmLclDte
dsucsuDiagFrmLclDte.description: This selection displays the status or controls the Local Channel Loopback for the selected channel. This is a local turnaround and is bi-directional. This selection is applicable only for CSU type channels.

dsucsuDiagFrmLclDte2.name: dsucsuDiagFrmLclDte2
dsucsuDiagFrmLclDte2.description: This selection displays the status or controls the Channel Remote Loopback for the selected channel. This loopback transmits a code to the remote node which will enable or disable a diagnostic loopback at the addressed channel. This selection is applicable only for CSU type channels.

dsucsuDiagFrmBertTestAct.name: dsucsuDiagFrmBertTestAct
dsucsuDiagFrmBertTestAct.description: BERT test related actions: a: Starts a BERT test on a channel, b: Stops a BERT test on a channel, c: Inject Errors while the BERT test is running, d: Clears BERT test errors.

dsucsuDiagFrmEvElapTime.name: dsucsuDiagFrmEvElapTime
dsucsuDiagFrmEvElapTime.description: The time elapsed since the PBX Event Test started. This selection is applicable only for PBX channels.

dsucsuDiagFrmEvBpvErr.name: dsucsuDiagFrmEvBpvErr
dsucsuDiagFrmEvBpvErr.description: The number of Bipolar Violations encountered during the Event Test. This selection is applicable only for PBX channels.

dsucsuDiagFrmEvOofErr.name: dsucsuDiagFrmEvOofErr
dsucsuDiagFrmEvOofErr.description: The number of Out-Of-Frame Errors encountered during the Event Test. This selection is applicable only for PBX channels.

dsucsuDiagFrmFrameErr.name: dsucsuDiagFrmFrameErr
dsucsuDiagFrmFrameErr.description: The number of Frame Errors encountered during the Event Test. This selection is applicable only for PBX channels.

dsucsuDiagFrmClearEvReg.name: dsucsuDiagFrmClearEvReg
dsucsuDiagFrmClearEvReg.description: Clears all the PBX Event Test registers. This selection is applicable only for PBX channels.

dsucsuDiagAuxSlot.name: dsucsuDiagAuxSlot
dsucsuDiagAuxSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuDiagAuxNode.name: dsucsuDiagAuxNode
dsucsuDiagAuxNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.

dsucsuDiagAuxChAStatus.name: dsucsuDiagAuxChAStatus
dsucsuDiagAuxChAStatus.description: Status of Supervisory link channel A.

dsucsuDiagAuxChBStatus.name: dsucsuDiagAuxChBStatus
dsucsuDiagAuxChBStatus.description: Status of Supervisory Link Channel B.

dsucsuDiagAuxMaintStatus.name: dsucsuDiagAuxMaintStatus
dsucsuDiagAuxMaintStatus.description: The Maint. Port Supervisory link status.

dsucsuDiagAuxCommStatus.name: dsucsuDiagAuxCommStatus
dsucsuDiagAuxCommStatus.description: The Communications port Supervisory link status.

dsucsuDiagPortSlot.name: dsucsuDiagPortSlot
dsucsuDiagPortSlot.description: The PC port to which the TyView node is attached.

dsucsuDiagPortNode.name: dsucsuDiagPortNode
dsucsuDiagPortNode.description: The node ID: unique per port ID.
